===Other engagements===
In addition to shows at their Saint Paul big top, Juventas students have also performed at the [[Mall of America]],<ref>{{cite news|last1=Moore|first1=Janet|last2=Kennedy|first2=Patrick|title=Megamall's success stirs a retail boom|url=http://search.proquest.com/docview/426877737|accessdate=June 17, 2014|work=[[Star Tribune]]|date=August 3, 1997}}{{subscription required|via=ProQuest}}</ref> the [[Saint Paul Winter Carnival]],<ref>{{cite news|last1=Shefchik|first1=Rick|title=New youth circus to help carnival hit new heights|url=http://infoweb.newsbank.com/iw-search/we/InfoWeb?p_product=AWNB&p_theme=aggregated5&p_action=doc&p_docid=0EB5DFF1EC925EA3&p_docnum=1&p_queryname=6|accessdate=June 17, 2014|work=[[St. Paul Pioneer Press]]|date=January 21, 1996}}{{subscription required|via=NewsBank}}</ref> [[Roy Wilkins Auditorium]],<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kimball|first1=Joe|title=Here's a plan for a St. Paul stadium|url=http://search.proquest.comdocview/427191759|accessdate=June 18, 2014|work=[[Star Tribune]]|date=November 12, 1999}}{{subscription required|via=ProQuest}}</ref> [[RiverCentre]],<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kimball|first1=Joe|title=Convention Bureau bids farewell to president|url=http://search.proquest.com/docview/427270952|accessdate=June 18, 2014|work=[[Star Tribune]]|date=May 19, 2000}}{{subscription required|via=ProQuest}}</ref> the [[Minnesota Children's Museum]],<ref>{{cite news|last1=Tomson|first1=Ellen|title=Sound bites|url=http://infoweb.newsbank.com.ezproxy.hclib.org/iw-search/we/InfoWeb?p_product=AWNB&p_theme=aggregated5&p_action=doc&p_docid=0EB739ABC464EFFA&p_docnum=15&p_queryname=5|accessdate=June 19, 2014|work=[[St. Paul Pioneer Press]]|date=April 25, 2000}}{{subscription required|via=NewsBank}}</ref> Minneapolis mayor [[R. T. Rybak]]'s 2002 inauguration at the [[Minneapolis City Hall]],<ref>{{cite news|last1=Olson|first1=Rochelle|title=Rybak outlines his inaugural events|url=http://search.proquest.com/docview/427459542|accessdate=June 20, 2014|work=[[Star Tribune]]|date=December 12, 2001}}{{subscription required|via=ProQuest}}</ref> the [[Ordway Center for the Performing Arts]] as part of the Flint Hills International Children's Festival,<ref>{{cite news|author1=BWW News Desk|title=Ordway Announces Children's Festival Lineup|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/st-paul/article/Ordway-Announces-Childrens-Festival-Lineup-20110511#|accessdate=July 22, 2014|work=BroadwayWorld|date=May 11, 2011}}</ref> on [[Ecolab]] Plaza,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kimball|first1=Joe|title=Dedicating, celebrating Bash welcomes futuristic 51-foot sculpture 'Skygate'|url=http://search.proquest.com/docview/427284158|accessdate=June 18, 2014|work=[[Star Tribune]]|date=June 9, 2000}}{{subscription required|via=ProQuest}}</ref> [[Nicollet Mall]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Taking commuting to a new level|url=http://search.proquest.com/docview/426982834|accessdate=June 18, 2014|work=[[Star Tribune]]|date=May 13, 1998}}{{subscription required|via=ProQuest}}</ref> and with the [[Shrine Circus]] in Minneapolis.<ref name="new home" /> Students have also participated non-Juventas shows, including a 2004 [[Minnesota Fringe Festival]] production,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Royce|first1=Graydon|title=Fringe Festival attendance rose 15.3%|url=http://search.proquest.com/docview/427650308|accessdate=June 20, 2014|work=[[Star Tribune]]|date=August 18, 2004}}{{subscription required|via=ProQuest}}</ref> the 2005 world premiere of ''Tin Forest'' with the [[Minnesota Orchestra]] at [[Orchestra Hall (Minneapolis)|Orchestra Hall]],<ref>{{cite news|last1=Grow|first1=Doug|title=Eine kleine kinder musik|url=http://search.proquest.com/docview/427694417|accessdate=June 20, 2014|work=[[Star Tribune]]|date=March 3, 2005}}{{subscription required|via=ProQuest}}</ref> the local [[Children's Theatre Company]]'s 2008 stage adaptation of ''[[Madeline and the Gypsies]]'',<ref>{{cite news|last1=Papatola|first1=Dominic P.|title=New 'Madeline' production is a real circus|url=http://www.twincities.com/stage/ci_10497808|accessdate=June 20, 2014|work=[[St. Paul Pioneer Press]]|date=September 19, 2008}}</ref> and the 2012 adaptation of [[Jack Prelutsky]]'s ''The Dragons Are Singing Tonight'' at [[The Southern Theater]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Shaver|first1=Connie|title=TigerLion Arts Presents The Dragons are Singing Tonight|url=http://www.knightarts.org/community/stpaul/tigerlion-arts-presents-the-dragons-are-singing-tonight|website=Knight Arts|publisher=John S. and James L. Knight Foundation|accessdate=June 24, 2014|date=January 4, 2012}}</ref> Outside of the [[Minneapolis<U+2013>Saint Paul]] area, Juventas students have traveled, including to perform at the RiverRocks Festival in [[Chattanooga, Tennessee]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Circus Juventas Performs At RiverRocks Oct. 8|url=http://chattanoogan.com/2010/9/20/184462/Circus-Juventas-Performs-At-RiverRocks.aspx|accessdate=June 24, 2014|work=[[The Chattanoogan]]|date=September 20, 2010}}</ref> and to compete, including at the International Circus Festival in [[Latina, Italy]],<ref>{{cite news|last1=Drewelow|first1=Rachel|title=St. Paul circus students will hit new heights in Italy|url=http://www.twincities.com/ci_10682634|accessdate=October 2, 2014|work=[[St. Paul Pioneer Press]]|date=October 10, 2008}}</ref> and at the Circus Ring of Friendship Festival in [[Norrk<U+00F6>ping|Norrk<U+00F6>ping, Sweden]], in which the troupe's [[triple trapeze]] team garnered the gold medal.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Tasto|first1=Erica|title=Circus Juventas trapeze team wins gold at Swedish competition|url=http://www.twincities.com/ci_16515200|accessdate=June 24, 2014|work=[[St. Paul Pioneer Press]]|date=November 4, 2010}}</ref>

==Music==
Much of the accompaniment for the big top summer shows came from local [[mandolin]] player [[Peter Ostroushko]].<ref name=PJtC /> Ostrouchko, known for his work on the radio show ''[[A Prairie Home Companion]]'',<ref name="grimm pipress">{{cite news|last1=Berdan|first1=Kathy|title=Under the magic big top, it's possible to be Grimm and happy at the same time|url=http://www.twincities.com/stage/ci_18567010|accessdate=June 18, 2014|work=[[St. Paul Pioneer Press]]|date=July 29, 2011}}</ref> became involved in the youth circus after his daughter saw a show and decided to join.<ref name=PJtC /> In 2005, upon discovering his affinity for the mandolin and [[fiddle]], the Butlers asked if Ostroushko would volunteer to play a [[Celtic music|Celtic]] song at the permiere of their upcoming summer big top show, ''Dyrnwych''.<ref name=PJtC /> He happily agreed, having expressed a lifelong dream of joining a circus, and played the track, "See It There/Con Cassidy's", not only at ''Dyrnwych''{{'s}} opening but also at each of its subsequent 18 performances.<ref name=PJtC /> The following year, he composed original music for the 2006 Juventas show, ''Pazzanni'', and expanded his band to five members, including himself on mandolin, fiddle, and [[mandocello]], Marc Anderson on percussion, Dan Chouinard on [[piano]], [[accordion]], and [[Electronic keyboard|keyboard]], Dirk Freymuth on electric and acoustic [[guitar]]s, and Joel Sayles on electric and acoustic [[bass guitar]]s.<ref name=PJtC /> Ostroushko again provided a score for ''Atlanticus'' and ''RavensManor'',<ref name=PJtC /> continued in 2010 with ''Sawdust'',<ref>{{cite news|title=Juventas tells story of the old traveling circus in "Sawdust"|url=http://aapress.com/arts/juventas-tells-story-of-the-old-traveling-circus-in-%E2%80%9Csawdust%E2%80%9D/|accessdate=June 18, 2014|work=Asian American Press|date=July 25, 2010}}</ref> then ''Grimm'',<ref name="grimm pipress" /> and finally ''Showdown''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Circus Juventas Provides Polished Showcase for Some Extraordinary Talent|url=http://spectaclemagazine.com/?page_id=2002|accessdate=June 18, 2014|work=Spectacle: An Online Journal of the Circus Arts|date=August 2012}}</ref> Tracks from the first four shows for which he played, from ''Dyrnwych'' to ''RavensManor'', are anthologized on the CD ''Peter Joins the Circus'', published by Borderland Productions in 2008.<ref name=PJtC />

==Reception==
Jando Dominique, reporting for ''Spectacle: An Online Journal of Circus Arts'', summarized audience and critical reception for Circus Juventas's shows by describing them as "always sold out and enthusiastically reviewed by the press".<ref name="expanding spectacle" /> Renee Valois cited the age of the performers and the proximity between them and the audience when she asked in a ''St. Paul Pioneer Press'' review of ''Oz'' comparing the circus school with Cirque du Soleil, "Dare I say Circus Juventas is more exciting than the troupe that inspired it?"<ref name=ozwonder>{{cite news|last1=Valois|first1=Renee|title=Circus Juventas' performance of 'Oz' is a wonder|url=http://www.twincities.com/stage/ci_23799191/circus-juventas-performance-oz-is-wonder|accessdate=June 23, 2014|work=[[St. Paul Pioneer Press]]|date=August 5, 2013}}</ref> Writing for ''Minnesota Monthly'', Amanda Bankston commended the technical skill and professionalism of the performers in 2012's ''Showdown'': "{{nowrap|[T]here}} is nothing child-like about the talent in this show. The budding stars fearlessly swing, flip, and soar through the air like pros."<ref name=youngfearless /> In ''Spectacle'', Dominique noted that Juventas's productions consistently have "a polish and style not often seen in youth circuses, or most professional ones, for that matter."<ref name="expanding spectacle" />

Susannah Schouweiler of Knight Arts wrote, "at two hours and 45 minutes, plus a 20-minute intermission, [''Grimm''{{'s}}] run time is an awfully long haul for the smallest circus-goers."<ref name=knightarts /> Critics have also commented on the occasional misstep in a performance; Rohan Preston noted in his review of ''Grimm'' that "there are moments -- just a few stand out -- when you realize that these are students, after all, in a celebrated after-school program. You want them to succeed, even if they do not always."<ref>{{cite news|last1=Preston|first1=Rohan|title=Fairy tales in flight|url=http://www.startribune.com/entertainment/stageandarts/126578298.html|accessdate=June 23, 2014|work=[[Star Tribune]]|date=August 2, 2011}}</ref> Similarly, writing for ''BroadwayWorld'', Elaina Lenertz stated, "Sometimes their silks routines are a bit out of sync and sometimes the show features dance routines from younger kids who are still mastering stunts. Despite this, the performance is very impressive."<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lenertz|first1=Elaina|title=Circus Juventas' SHOWDOWN Wows Audiences with Pint-Sized Performers|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/minneapolis/article/BWW-Reviews-Circus-Juventas-SHOWDOWN-Wows-Audiences-with-Pint-Sized-Performers-20120822|accessdate=June 23, 2014|work=BroadwayWorld|date=August 22, 2012}}</ref>

